column5: Beauty browns right there!!!
Thanks Bob. Theres 8 guys in our group that will be lookin for the tags. I should have a few pictures when the derby's over.
Nice shooting Dave
nice fish! can you eat them in moderation out of lake ontario?

Took my stepson out for a little fishin time this morning. Picked up 4 Browns this morning east of Grimsby plus one small Coho. 1 Brown missing in the pictures because of a big Lamprey hole in the side. All fish caught under 15 FTW
nice looking, fat, healthy fish, way to go
Nice shootin FF....Guide service in the makin
Thanks Guys, Trolled by this place. I didn't want to get to close.
Nice Dave!
Great browns.  There such cool fish and the spring reports are always appreciated.
Great fishing.   Those are all real chunky brownies to boot!
Nice fish  , but a "guide service"   he said he was east but the pics look like west of Grimsby .  Surprised the pier is so empty

Hy, your good, no pulling the wool over your eyes  . I never thought of the back ground. Those pictures are west, almost to the rifle range. We had them in the live-well, my stepson wanted fish for the smoker plus his picture taken to show the boys at work. But to be honest we did catch them east of Grimsby
Nice work Dave    Great looking brown   Congrats
They're very nice looking fish. Wish we had them up here. Good job Dave.
Beautiful!!  You guys are killing me  Can't wait to get out there again!

To be honest, I've always found the area of the pics better for browns than east of Grimsby, maybe in a little tighter than the pics appear. Even shore casting there better than the now famous pier, the pier for me seems to have a lake trout jinx East seems to be better for spring kings though, out deeper than you find the browns though and look for structure.
awesome
Nice clean fish Dave.
nice going. Got my finger crossed the winds wont be too bad Sunday and maybe I can get out again
some very nice fat browns for sure !!!well done...
Show off!
nice browns dave

Thanks Guys, I should be out there today but getting ready for the 3 weeks at the Orillia Perch Festival. Leaving Sunday for our first 4 days, 8 guys. Home for 2 days and back up for ? days. Hope to see some OFC'ers looking for the Tags.  Get back to work you.   Be by this morning for a coffee.   You going to the swap? I'll pick you up
Very impressive fish there Dave. Just one like that in my season and I'll be HAPPY! Congrats!
Thanks Roy Those fish were caught not to far from chris's place, maybe 10 min's Roy. They have been doing well this week there. Shame your last trip down here wasn't this week.
Gotta love spring Browns!!!
Another GREAT FARM REPORT.....  Always loved the look of those browns......   NOW GO CATCH them there perch....you know...the ones with tags...  GOOD LUCK, Bob
